  "description": [
    "Hationcl Engineers Week OFWCE OF THE MAYOR TOWN OF TAZEWELL PROCLAMATION WHEREAS the week o Wash ingtons Birthday is observed by Professional Engineering Societies as National Engineers Week and WHEREAS it is recognized that modern civilization has benefited widely through the application of scientific principles by engineers thus building broader horizons for all and WHEREAS the rapid world population increase requires con tinued economic growth to pre vent social chaos and WHEREAS members of the En gineering Profession must contin ue their contributions towards the creation development and constriction of the industrial com plex And community services so necessary to continued economic growth throughout the State Nat ion and the World and WHEREAS National Engineers Week will be observed in the town of Tazewell Virginia by appropri ate displays and activities NOW Therefore I James W Harman Jr Mayor of the Town of Tazewell do hereby proclaim the period of February 18 to 24 1962 as Engineers Week in Tazewell and urge every citizen of Tazewell to join me in participating in the activities and in extending recog nition and honor to our engineers Dated this 17th day of February A D 1962 James W Harman Jr Mayor THE WHITE"
